## First run — bootstrap a fresh project

When this repo is created from the template (via "Use this template" or
`gh repo create --template atilcan65/dev-studio-template`), do this once:

### Prerequisite: PROJECT_TOKEN PAT (one-time per machine)

The board-sync workflow (ADR-0013) needs a classic PAT with `repo` +
`project` scopes — default `GITHUB_TOKEN` cannot mutate ProjectsV2.
See **ADR-0014** for the full rationale.

1. Open <https://github.com/settings/tokens> → "Generate new token
   (classic)".
2. Name it `dev-studio PROJECT_TOKEN`, expiration 90 days (or your
   policy).
3. Tick the **`repo`** and **`project`** scope boxes.
4. Copy the `ghp_...` value.
5. Add to your shell rc (so every new project picks it up automatically):
   ```bash
   export PROJECT_TOKEN=ghp_xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx
   ```
6. `source ~/.bashrc` (or open a new shell).

The **same PAT is reused across every project** — that's the point of
using a classic (not fine-grained) PAT. If you forget the `export`,
`dev-studio-init.sh` will prompt you (hidden input) on first run.

### Bootstrap

```bash
# 1. clone & enter
git clone https://github.com/{{GITHUB_OWNER}}/{{GITHUB_REPO}}.git
cd {{GITHUB_REPO}}

# 2. render all .tmpl files with values pulled from `gh` and `git`,
#    and write PROJECT_TOKEN to the repo secret (ADR-0014)
bash scripts/dev-studio-init.sh

# 3. start the multi-agent watcher
bash scripts/dev-studio-start.sh start

# 4. open the first issue with label `agent:product-manager` so PM
#    runs the vision-intake flow (see .claude/CLAUDE.md §Product)
gh issue create \
  --title "Project kickoff — vision intake" \
  --label "agent:product-manager"
```

The init script is idempotent — re-running it always produces a clean
render from the latest `.tmpl` files. Edits made to rendered outputs
(e.g. this `README.md`, `.claude/CLAUDE.md`) will be overwritten; edit
the corresponding `*.tmpl` instead.

